<% layout("/layouts/boilerplate") %>

<div class="legal-page container py-4">
  <div class="legal-card">
    <h1 class="legal-title">Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p class="legal-updated">Last updated: June 2026</p>

    <p>
      Stayora respects your privacy. This Privacy Policy explains what information may be collected when you use the platform, how that information is used, and the choices available to users.
    </p>

    <h3>Information We Collect</h3>
    <p>Depending on how you use Stayora, the following information may be collected:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Name, username, email address, and login-related information during account creation.</li>
      <li>Listing details submitted by hosts, including title, description, price, location, country, and uploaded images.</li>
      <li>Booking-related details such as selected check-in and check-out dates.</li>
      <li>Reviews, ratings, wishlist activity, and other actions performed inside the app.</li>
      <li>Technical information such as browser type, device details, and basic request data for security and performance.</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>How We Use Information</h3>
    <p>Information collected through Stayora may be used to:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Create and manage user accounts.</li>
      <li>Display, create, edit, and manage listings.</li>
      <li>Enable wishlist, booking, and review functionality.</li>
      <li>Improve user experience, app performance, and platform reliability.</li>
      <li>Protect the platform against misuse, spam, or unauthorized activity.</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Third-Party Services</h3>
    <p>
      Stayora may use third-party services such as Cloudinary for image hosting, Mapbox for maps and location display, MongoDB Atlas for database storage, and Render for deployment. These services may process limited technical or usage-related data as required for their functionality.
    </p>

    <h3>Data Sharing</h3>
    <p>
      Stayora does not sell personal information. Information may be shared only when necessary to operate platform features, comply with applicable laws, or protect the app, its users, and its services.
    </p>

    <h3>Data Security</h3>
    <p>
      Reasonable steps are taken to protect account and platform data. However, no online service can guarantee complete security, and users should also use strong passwords and protect their login credentials.
    </p>

    <h3>User Content</h3>
    <p>
      Listings, reviews, profile-related data, and uploaded images submitted by users may be visible to other users depending on platform functionality.
    </p>

    <h3>Changes to This Policy</h3>
    <p>
      This Privacy Policy may be updated from time to time as the project evolves. Continued use of Stayora after changes means users accept the updated policy.
    </p>

    <h3>Contact</h3>
    <p>
      For questions about this Privacy Policy, users can contact the project owner through the portfolio or repository contact details associated with Stayora.
    </p>
  </div>
</div>